### Bug Scenario and Root Cause

The image shows a tooltip displaying a title when hovering over a dropdown item in a Cascader component. The bug report requests an API to remove the title information from the tooltip. The root cause is likely that the title attribute is being set automatically, and there is no current option to disable it.

### Bug Location and Analysis

In the provided code snippet from `src/cascader/cascader.jsx`, the `Cascader` component does not have a prop or method to control the display of the title attribute. We need to add a new prop to allow users to disable the title.

### Patches

To fix the issue, we will add a new prop `showTitle` to control the display of the title attribute. By default, it will be `true` to maintain current behavior, but users can set it to `false` to remove the title.

